    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Attachments can then be added/removed directly by the caller, using Core Foundation APIs. On return, the caller doesnâ€™t own the returned array of attachments dictionaries, and must retain it if the caller needs to maintain a reference to it. If there are no sample attachments yet, and createIfNecessary is true, a new ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "CFArray",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " containing N empty ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "CFMutableDictionaries",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " is returned (where N is the number of samples in the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "CMSampleBuffer",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": "), so that attachments can be added directly by the caller. If there are no sample attachments yet, and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "createIfNecessary",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " is false, ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "NULL",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " is returned. Once the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "CFArray",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " has been created, subsequent calls will return it, even if there are still no sample attachments in the array.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
